seed_data.description: Lawyers' desks are notoriously covered in paperwork, but Harvey can make all that clutter disappear. The AI company is built to securely store thousands of sensitive documents – including court records – and quickly allow lawyers to get answers to complex legal queries. Winston Weinberg and Gabriel Pereyra cofounded the startup in 2022, and in the past year it has grown from 40 customers to 235, including the majority of top 10 U.S. law firms. Recently, the startup raised a $300 million series E round, boosting its valuation to $5 billion, and announced plans to expand coverage to India, Australia and Germany.
